        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add local WebVNC bridge",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add `crabbox webvnc local` for an existing macOS/Linux loopback VNC tunnel\n- reuse the embedded noVNC viewer and token-gated in-memory credential handoff\n- pin the source to one current-user process identity and stop on replacement\n- bound unauthenticated HTTP headers and credential request bodies\n\n## Security boundary\n\n- source and browser listeners remain on literal `127.0.0.1`\n- the VNC password is accepted only through stdin and stays out of argv, environment variables, URLs, and viewer files\n- every VNC connection revalidates the listener PID and process-start identity before and after dialing\n- the temporary viewer is mode `0600` and contains only a short-lived bridge token\n\n## Verification\n\n- `go test ./internal/cli -run 'Test(MacOSWebVNC|WebVNCLocal|ServeLocalWebVNCBridge|LocalWebVNCListenerIdentity|ReadLocalWebVNCPassword|ExactLocalWebVNCListenerOwnerPID)' -count=1`\n- `go test ./internal/cli`\n- `go vet ./...`\n- Linux and Windows cross-compilation of `./internal/cli`\n- `node scripts/build-docs-site.mjs`\n",
